summary:
Here is a summarized version of the Security Council document:

The Security Council,

Noting the tense situation in the Middle East, 
Having considered the report of the Secretary-General on UNDOF, 
Stressing the importance of the 1974 Disengagement of Forces Agreement, 

1. Calls upon parties to implement resolution 338 (1973);
2. Stresses parties' obligation to respect the Disengagement of Forces Agreement, 
   exercise maximum restraint, prevent ceasefire breaches, and 
   encourages parties to use UNDOF's liaison function; 

Condemns continued fighting, use of heavy weapons in the area of separation, 
and stresses no military forces should be present except UNDOF; 

Urges parties to cease military actions, respect international humanitarian law; 

Reaffirms readiness to consider listing individuals, groups supporting ISIL, 
Al-Nusra Front under sanctions regime; 

Recognizes need for flexible adjustment of UNDOF's posture to minimize security risks; 

Emphasizes importance of access to reports and information on UNDOF's configuration; 

Underscores need for UNDOF to have necessary means and resources; 

Expresses appreciation to UNDOF personnel, condemns incidents threatening their safety;
